<DATELINE>BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ernest Gaines, best known for the
television adaptation of his work, ``The Autobiography of Miss Jane
Pittman,'' was named Louisiana's Humanist of the Year.
   ``Gaines is at once an historian, psychologist, and sociologist
of the Louisiana he loves so much,'' Dr. James Olney, chairman of
the Louisiana Endowment for the Humanities, said Thursday.
   His works include ``The Sky is Gray,'' ``A Gathering of Old
Men,'' ``Bloodline'' and ``Of Love and Dust.''
   Gaines, 56, has been professor of creative writing and
writer-in-residence at the University of Southwestern Louisiana
since 1984.
