<FIRST>u i AM-Japan-Markets     12-08 0153</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Japan-Markets,0159</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dollar Rises, Stocks Fall in Tokyo</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar rose against the yen in Tokyo Friday,
while stock prices dropped back.
   The dollar closed at 144.27 yen, up 0.14 yen from its close of
144.13 yen on Thursday. After opening at 144.32 yen, the U.S.
currency ranged between 144.20 and 144.40 yen during the day.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average
finished the week at 37,724.06, down 134.05 points from Thursday's
record-high closing of 37,858.11.
   Volume on the market's first section was estimated at 1 billion
shares.
   A trader at Kleinwort Benson securities said he didn't expect
that the market's recent rally, in which the Nikkei average
advanced in all but two of the past 22 trading days, had ended
despite Friday's drop.
   ``There are a lot of people still waiting to put money into the
market,'' said the trader on condition of anonymity.
