<HEAD>Tour Bus Crash Kills Three, Injures Eight</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AUBURN HILLS, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A car slammed into a bus carrying
about 60 people to a Christmas concert, killing the three men in
the car and injuring eight on the bus, police said.
   The driver and seven passengers on the bus were treated at
Pontiac General Hospital after the wreck Thursday evening. One
remained hospitalized today with broken ribs and the rest were
treated and released, said police Sgt. Jerry Knapp said.
   The bus, taking employees from a grocery store chain to a
Christmas outing to see singer Marie Osmond, was hit by the car as
the bus turned into a parking lot, police said. The bus frame
twisted, crushing the car as it came to rest under the rear of the
bus.
   The men were removed from the mangled car by rescuers using
``jaws of life'' equipment and pronounced dead at the scene, Knapp
said. Knapp said he didn't know who was at fault in the crash.
   Victims of the crash were identified as Robert Lowry, 39, of
Lake Orion and John Breeze II, 38, and Edward French, 36, both of
Pontiac, Knapp said.
