<HEAD>U.S. Envoy Seeks Extension On Greek Bases Closing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   U.S. Ambassador Michael Sotirhos asked
Friday for a six-month extension in the deadline for closing U.S.
bases in Greece.
   Constantine Mitsotakis, leader of the Conservative New Democracy
party, said Sotirhos made the request at a meeting.
   A Greek-U.S. defense agreement for four major U.S. military
bases in Greece expired in December 1988. The Americans must
dismantle the bases by May 1990 if no new pact is signed.
Negotations remain deadlocked after 17 rounds of talks.
   Talks were frozen after inconclusive general elections here on
June 18 and Nov. 5.
   Mitsotakis said Premier Xenophon Zolotas' government would look
into the U.S. request.
