<HEAD>Five Killed in Prison Battle</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Federal police stormed a prison
Friday to stop fighting between rival inmates that killed five
prisoners and left 41 wounded, officials reported.
   About 40 prisoners broke through a cell partition and attacked
another group of inmates with knives and clubs, according to
Marilena Viania, director of the Evaristo de Moraes prison in
northern Rio.
   She said 200 federal police entered the prison early Friday and
ended the six-hour battle.
   The director said 20 of the injured prisoners were in serious
condition with stab wounds.
   ``It was a power struggle between inmates that got out of
hand,'' she told The Associated Press by telephone. ``For awhile,
it looked as if the whole prison might join the revolt.''
   She said the prison housed 1,300 inmates.
