<HEAD>Grenade Explodes at Manila Post Office</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An attacker hurled a grenade into the
capital's crowded main post office Saturday, injuring at least 16
people, police and hospital sources said.
   It was not clear whether the attack was related to the recent
attempt by mutinous soldiers to topple President Corazon Aquino.
   Police Lt. Jun Javier of the homicide section said the M-26
fragmentation grenade was hurled at an area of the first floor
where employees were selling stamps.
   At least 16 people were taken to the nearby Philippine General
Hospital. There were no reports of any fatalities, Javier said.
