<DOCNO> AP891208-0257 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-12-08-89 1341EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f AM-MortgageRates     12-08 0070</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Mortgage Rates,0074</SECOND>
<HEAD>Fixed-Rate Mortgages Average 9.76 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fixed-rate home mortgages are currently
averaging 9.76 percent, according to a national survey released
Friday by the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp.
   That rate was up from a rate of 9.74 percent last week.
   On one-year adjustable rate mortgages, lenders were asking an
average initial rate of 8.39 percent this week, down from 8.46
percent the week before.
</TEXT>
