<FIRST>r f BC-EllisHorwood-Paramount     12-08 0117</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Ellis Horwood-Paramount,0123</SECOND>
<HEAD>Simon &amp; Schuster Acquires Ellis Horwood Ltd.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Paramount Communications Inc.'s Simon &amp; Schuster
publishing unit said Friday it had acquired Ellis Horwood Ltd., a
leading British publisher of computer science, mathematics,
engineering and science titles.
   Terms of the deal were not disclosed.
   Henry Hirschberg, president of Simon &amp; Schuster's international
publishing group, said acquisition of the privetly-held Ellis
Horwood ``fits perfectly with our strategic commitment to growth
through acquisition of top-quality products.''
   Ellis Horwood was founded in 1973 and is based in Chichester,
England. It has published 800 titles and is expected to publish 150
titles in 1990.
   Simon &amp; Schuster publishes consumer, educational and
professional information material worldwide.
</TEXT>
