<FIRST>r f AM-Fireman'sName     12-08 0191</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Fireman's Name,0198</SECOND>
<HEAD>Holding Company Changes Name</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GREENWICH, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fireman's Fund Corp. changed its name to
Fund American Cos. Inc. Friday to erase confusion between the
holding company and its insurance subsidiary and to return to a
name it used 21 years ago.
   The corporation's board of directors decided to retain the name
Fireman's Fund Insurance Co. for the subsidiary, while creating a
separate identity for the holding company.
   ``The Fireman's Fund name originated 126 years ago in insurance.
That's where the name belongs,'' said Jack Byrne, corporation
chairman.
   ``By reintroducing the name Fund American, the holding company
is enhancing corporate identity, allowing the name Fireman's Fund
to be reserved exclusively for our insurance company.''
   The name Fund American was used from 1965 until 1968, when the
corporation was bought by American Express. When the business was
sold in a public offering in 1985, the company established the name
Fireman's Fund Corp. for the holding company.
   Fireman's Fund, which sells property and casualty insurance and
is based in Novato, Calif., is the only subsidiary of Fund
American, a Greenwich-based corporation. It had $3.7 billion in
sales last year.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
