<SECOND>AM-Auto Recall,0106</SECOND>
<HEAD>Mazda Recalls Minivans</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mazda Motor Corp. on Friday recalled 10,587 1989
minivans with seven-passenger seating to replace seat-belt brackets.
   The company said in a news release that the brackets on the
third seat may not be strong enough to meet federal standards and
could fail in the event of an accident.
   Mazda spokesman Fred Aikins said the company was unaware of any
accidents or injuries associated with the problem. The problem was
discovered during National Highway Traffic Safety Administration
tests.
   Owners are being notified by mail and repairs will be performed
free of charge.
